<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2440] Add support for custom ExecutorServices in ParallelMultiSearcher</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2440</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, the ParallelMultiSearcher uses a cachedThreadPool, which is limitless and a poor choice for a web application, given the threaded nature of the requests (say a webapp with tomcat-default 200 threads and 100 indexes could be looking at 2000 searching threads pretty easily).  Support for adding a custom ExecutorService is pretty trivial.  Patch forthcoming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Any&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
